   In a bitter memo to employees, Mr. Hagopian added: "We are convinced that we won the resolicitation competition. 
Someday, we will know for sure, when the Freedom of Information Act allows us to get into that." 
He elaborated in the interview that he believes the Army had decided to choose Ayer, but changed its mind after Ayer was suspended from government bidding. 

