Other bidders were Ogilvy &amp; Mather, Chicago, a unit of New York-based Ogilvy Group Inc.; and Woodbridge, Va.-based Wilmar Group Ltd. 

   New York-based Ayer's suspension from bidding was based on Army charges that Ayer falsified time cards from 1979 to 1983 and submitted noncompetitive bids through a scheme with subcontractors. 
The Army also said that a former Ayer vice president pleaded guilty to accepting kickbacks. 

